    <h1>Buy&#xAD;ing out the Mag&#xAD;pies</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200818/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-18"><time>2020-08-18</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>OC­TO­BER 2017</p>
    <p>Owner Mike Ash­ley of­fi­cially puts New­cas­tle up for sale, 10 years af­ter buy­ing the club.</p>
    <p>OC­TO­BER 2018</p>
    <p>Bri­tish fi­nancier Amanda Stave­ley walks away from a po­ten­tial deal with Ash­ley.</p>
    <p>MARCH 2020</p>
    <p>Stave­ley, along­side Saudi Ara­bia’s sov­er­eign wealth fund and Bri­tish prop­erty bil­lion­aire broth­ers, David and Si­mon Reuben, an­nounce a pro­posed takeover for £350 mil­lion (S$627.1 mil­lion).</p>
    <p>JULY 2020</p>
    <p>The consortium’s bid col­lapses af­ter it de­clines to take up the Premier League’s of­fer of in­de­pen­dent ar­bi­tra­tion to de­cide the club’s owner.</p>
    <p>AU­GUST 2020</p>
    <p>The Sin­ga­pore-backed Bel­la­graph Nova Group, whose web­site re­veals a net worth of $15.6 bil­lion, re­veals it is in ad­vanced talks with New­cas­tle over a takeover.</p>


